DATA_DELTA_POOL_HISTORY_MAX - Static variable in class de.cau.cs.kieler.sim.kiem.execution.JSONDataPool
This is the maximum number of consecutive new entries that will be kept in history for a delta update meaning that between two consecutive calls of getDeltaData there should not be more than DATA_DELTA_POOL_HISTORY_MAX new entries been produced (regardless of any steps!) note that the dataDeltePool is needed for Delta Observer and for history steps only.
